                   The Company has provided for taxes on the income of its
              manufacturing subsidiary's operations in Puerto Rico at an
              effective rate that is lower than the U.S. federal income tax
              statutory rate. This rate reflects the fact that approximately 90%
              of income is exempt from local taxes in Puerto Rico as well as the
              availability of a tax credit under Section 936 of the Internal
              Revenue Code. Withholding taxes at a negotiated rate of 7% (6% in
              1993 and 5% in 1992) have been provided on the expected
              repatriation of the income of this subsidiary.

