              NOTE K - COMMITMENTS AND CONTINGENCIES
              
              The Company is engaged in litigation as a defendant in cases
              involving alleged patent infringement, product liability claims
              and shareholders' derivative and class action suits (see Item 
              3).  In the opinion of management, based upon advice of 
              counsel, the ultimate outcome of these lawsuits should not 
              have a material adverse effect on the Company's consolidated 
              financial statements.

                   As part of the ongoing expansion of its Puerto Rico 
              operations, the Company is committed to certain undertakings,
              including the maintenance of specified levels of employment and
              capitalization for the Puerto Rican subsidiary.





